#DOC id=03--advisory-council--war-room source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/03--advisory-council--war-room.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.297Z

S|# 03 · Advisory Council (+ War Room)|> The owner's "board of strategic advisors" — five distinct agents with full mem access who debate, recommend, and can be convened into a live **War Room** ses. The closing showcase of the walkthrough.
S|Purpose|In the old system the advisory council under-performed because the advisor agents only had narrow knw of a few projects. With the new mem system, **five distinct agents with different roles get complete knw-base access.** They produce recommendations, debate topics, surface the patterns of what the owner keeps thinking about, and can be turned into an audio "podcast" to listen to (each agt gets a distinct **HeyGen** voice).
S|Page header|- Title: **Advisory Council**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / Advisory Council`. // - Buttons: **Set today's topic** and **Run a live ses** (opens the War Room). // - Tabs/sections: **Recommendations**, **Outcomes / rv**, **Strategic Archive**.
S|Today's recommendation (hero)|- A headline recommendation, e.g. *"Productize the agt-as-a-service offer now — turn the 'I run your agents' service into a fixed €2k/mo retainer, before the category name consolidates."* // - A **proposed-by** line crediting the agt(s) (e.g. a "needs your call / rv" badge). // - A **First step** suggestion (concrete next action), e.g. "Package the Maria engagement as the template … and pitch it to your two warmest leads this week." // - An **audio player** — a waveform/podcast-style player (e.g
S|Recommendations list|Below the hero, a stack of further recommendations (e.g. "Slow down the app-factory bet — prove By Design's retention before building #2"), each tagged (Product, str, fin…), credited to one or more council agents, with the same accept/assign/ask actions.
S|Pattern Tracker (right rail)|- **Pattern Tracker** — surfaces recurring themes the council keeps raising ("Productize, stop doing bespoke," "Focus → fewer bets, deeper," "Repackage, don't re-create," "Get Wolf to put fin on it…"). This acts as a **mirror** showing the owner which topics are most urgent/most discussed. // - **"This month"** — a count/summary of topics discussed this period.
S|Setting topics & live sessions|- **Set today's topic / set a topic for a particular day** — the owner can queue a specific question for which they want strategic input, framed as a debate. // - **Run a live ses** — launches the **War Room** (below).
S|War Room (live session modal)|A full-screen, cinematic live str room (a rendered 3D conference room — a cliffside cave with a round table and a city/ocean view at dusk). // - **Header:** `WAR ROOM`, a "Live ses" indicator, **Pause** and **Skip** controls, the debate topic (e.g. *"Should I raise consulting rates 20% for new leads?"*), and a **LIVE** badge. // - **Left transcript rail:** a running live chat of the debate — each agt (You, Strategist, Nexus, …) speaks in turn with timestamped lines, arguing different angles (the
S|Agents & voices (design intent)|Five role-distinct advisor agents, each with full knw-base access and a unique HeyGen voice, briefed heavily on what kinds of recommendations/topics they should cover. The output doubles as a listenable podcast.